Place the beef, onions and carrots into a 3 1/2- to 6-quart slow cooker. Sprinkle with the flour and toss to coat. Stir the broth, vegetable juice and brown sugar in a medium bowl. Pour the broth mixture over the beef and vegetables. Submerge the Bouquet Garni into the broth mixture. Cover and cook on LOW for 8 to 9 hours* or until the beef is fork-tender. Remove the Bouquet Garni. Serve the beef mixture over the noodles.